AU  - Egreteau, D.
TI  - Barriers to resilience: chronic poverty, climate change and disasters in the southwest of Bangladesh.
T2  - Field Exchange - Emergency Nutrition Network ENN
M3  - Journal article
AB  - The objective of this study was to capture the driving factors of chronic poverty and the impacts of climate change on livelihoods in the southwest coastal belt of Bangladesh, as well as to identify levels of disaster resilience and existing coping strategies being utilized. Attention was given to the dangerous conversion from rice to shrimp production in the region. What was found was a complex array of interlinking factors which together, present significant barriers to livelihood opportunities and sustainable development for communities, and the region as a whole. To improve the resilience of livelihoods and coping capacity of this agro-dependant region, several adaptive measures are suggested.
