AB  - This collection of eight papers focuses on issues concerning gender and climate change in India. Topics addressed include: the gender dimensions of groundwater dependence; gendered vulnerabilities to floods; climate change-induced migration and the coping strategies by left-behind women farmers; household drought coping and food insecurity; changes in women's use of energy in agriculture and their potential in reducing greenhouse gas emissions; and gender sensitive climate information communication.
