TI  - The assessment of the socioeconomic impacts of climate change at household level and policy implications.
T2  - Building resilience for adaptation to climate change in the agriculture sector. Proceedings of a Joint FAO/OECD Workshop, Rome, Italy, 23-24 April 2012
M3  - Book chapter
M3  - Conference paper
AB  - The objective of the present paper is to assist in describing a framework that could be employed to assess the socio-economic impacts of weather shocks and climate changes on agricultural households and particularly farmers in developing countries. Sections of the paper discuss: (i) a framework for the assessment of impacts resulting from climate changes and weather shocks in food security at household level; (ii) the use of two methodological tools that are able to assess the vulnerability to food insecurity as well as the resilience of farming households to the incidence of climate change and extreme events; (iii) preliminary evidence on the welfare losses measured by increases in poverty, food insecurity breakthroughs or health-related impacts; and; (iv) an outline of key policy messages for successful adaptation options at household level and particularly for farmers.
