TI  - Climate risk assessment for selected value chain commodities in Rwanda.
T2  - Climate risk assessment for selected value chain commodities in Rwanda
M3  - Miscellaneous
AB  - This assessment of climate risk for six value chain commodities (beans, cassava, potatoes, maize, tomatoes, and milk) was conducted across 12 districts in Rwanda. The vulnerability of the six commodities is discussed in relation to its sensitivity to change, coping and adaptive capacity, and the risks of climate change on agriculture and small-scale farmers in the 12 districts assessed. Results show that beans, maize and cassava will gain new areas for cultivation and this translates to new opportunities for more production while potatoes and tomatoes will lose suitable areas, translating to reduction in production. Milk production is set to gain and lose in two fronts: (i) increase in areas suitable for cultivation of feed, i.e. Napier; and (ii) heat stress for animals is projected to increase, thus affecting dairy cattle by reducing production.
