TI  - Small-scale farmers, big-scale change.
T2  - Farming Matters
M3  - Journal article
AB  - The possibility of reversing high dependence on agrichemical inputs on a large scale, particularly among family farmers who work in close-knit networks, is illustrated in this paper by the experiences of the Centre for Sustainable Agriculture (CSA) in Andhra Pradesh, India. In CSA's experience, two successful strategies for scaling up took place: collaboration between NGOs and the government, and scaling up by farmers themselves, as they adopt the concept of non-pesticidal management (NPM) and adapt it to their local conditions.
