AB  - Results are presented from a preliminary investigation into the feasibility of fish culture in "kole" or river ponds in Bangladesh as a climate change adaptation initiated by fishers. River drying and limited fishing scope in the dry season is now a regular phenomenon that has prompted fishers to initiate fish farming in river ponds as an alternative livelihood option.
