TI  - Analysis of the role of livelihood diversity to rural household resilience in drought condition: case study of the drought exposed areas of Isfahan province.
T2  - Rural Research
M3  - Journal article
AB  - This study assessed the livelihood strategies of farmer households in 12 villages in Isfahan province (Iran) that have been affected to varying degrees by drought and with different levels of development. The results showed that the livelihood approach adopted by families living in drought conditions has led them to greater resilience, and that the severity of drought increases the diversity of rural livelihoods. These results indicate that in villages with long experience of drought, livelihood diversification is a key strategy adopted by households to deal with this crisis.
