TI  - Special Issue: Local evidence on vulnerabilities and adaptations to global environmental change.
T2  - Global Environmental Change
M3  - Journal issue
AB  - This special issue examines local evidence on vulnerabilities and adaptations to global environmental change. The issue consists of five articles. The first article examines the coping mechanisms and adaptive strategies adopted by farming households in three villages in Shandong Province. The second article applies an agent-based framework that considers the behavioural model of farmers in three villages in a municipality in the Philippines. The third article presents a participatory approach to investigate vulnerability and adaptive capacity to climate variability and water stress in the Lakhwar watershed in Uttarakhand State, India. The fourth article presents evidence on two distinct farming systems - one that utilizes common property pasturelands and another based on private pasturelands - in the Brazilian semi-arid zone. The fifth article examines how climatic events affect agricultural livelihoods.
