AB  - A Water Research Commission (WRC)-funded research process is exploring best practice options for climate resilient agriculture for smallholders in South Africa. The research process is broadly divided into three elements: (1) community climate change adaptation process design; (2) climate resilient agricultural practices; and (3) a decision support system. This article focuses on the design of the community level process, and summarizes the results of climate change dialogues. These dialogues allowed groups of farmers to explore the impacts of climate change and potential adaptive strategies, and to prioritise local adaptation measures.
