AB  - A gender analysis is presented of the progress report on the implementation of Odisha's Climate Change Action Plan for 2010-2015 with respect to health, agriculture and forestry. Some observations and suggestions are also presented with respect to these three sectors plus disaster management in the Climate Change Action Plan for 2015-2020. It is concluded that gender needs to be a cross cutting issue across all sectors. Specific methodologies which are useful to achieve gender sensitivity of adaptation strategies are outlined.
