AB  - This special issue aims to highlight the relevance of culture to sustainable development in mountains. Topics covered by the six articles include: the potential of the Cultural Route heritage category as an instrument for cultural revitalization and rural development; the adaptive strategies adopted by herders against the decollectivization of rangelands; the transmission and transformation of (agri)-cultural values of mountain farming through farm-based educational services; change, collective action, and cultural resilience in mountain grassland management; the influence of values and worldviews on the resilience of tourism to natural hazards; and the transformation of traditional hospitality under the influence of tourism development.
