T2  - Food Policy
M3  - Journal issue
AB  - This special issue contains 15 articles on fertilizer and soil health policies, discussing topics such as: economic shocks; smallholder farming; global shocks to fertilizer markets; leveraging agricultural production organizations to reduce fertilizer use in China; Kenyan fertilizer markets response to the fuel-fertilizer-food price crisis; direct and indirect effects of weather shocks on fertilizer and improved seeds use; site-specific soil-test-based extension advice on farm management in Malawi; economic consequences of fertilizer supply shocks; deconstructing fertilizer price hikes; input subsidies, fertilizer intensity and imbalances amidst climate change in Bangladesh; fertilizer policy reforms in the midst of crisis in Rwanda; maize yield responsiveness and profitability of fertilizer; fertilizer demand and profitability amid global fuel-food-fertilizer crisis in Ethiopia; early growing season temperature variation and fertilizer use among smallholder farmers; and evidence of fertilizer and conflicts in Myanmar.
