AU  - Jahromi, A. B.
TI  - The analysis of nomads' production economics and their income: case of Darzeh, Kahnooj, Kerman Province, Iran.
T2  - American-Eurasian Journal of Agricultural and Environmental Science
M3  - Journal article
AB  - This paper studies the attributes and economics of production by nomads in Darzeh, Kahnooj (Iran). Data were collected by participatory approach (PRA) using triangulation techniques and then analysed. The study covered 18 tribal communities. In each tribal community, data collection was done separately using participatory approaches. Livestock raising and orchards (date palm) were the main sources of income of the nomads. Recently, they are threatened by drought and their productivity has increased. Also, handicraft industry is not common in this society. In total, employment rate is about 68%. Findings show that although livestock raising is considered as the main source of nomads' income, most of their income come from wage labour (939000000 rials, US$ 93900), horticulture (90750000 rials, US$ 9075), livestock raising (77680000 rials, US$ 7768) and handicraft (25000000 rials, US$ 2500), respectively. Per capita income is about 564000 rials (US$ 56.4), which is so low. Designing proper strategies for their sedentarisation, programming for agricultural education development in order to increase their farm productivity, paying attention to cultural affairs, offering bank facilities, organizing nomads in local associations and building local dams, are some of the suggestions to improve the nomads' situation.
